<node TEXT="there are some fundamental differences in underwater vision compared to vision in air. First, while still propagating through the water, light rays are absorbed and scattered when single photons encounter particles in the water or water molecules. Even more severe however, are effects caused by refraction. Refraction occurs&#xd;&#xa;when a light ray enters the underwater housing and passes from water through glass into air. Those changes of media cause the ray to change its direction and therefore leads to geometrical distortions." ID="ID_939498546" CREATED="1501289647175" MODIFIED="1501289647175" LINK="project://15D6452E29D9SKCYL8S32EEF1MB7Z0BV75KJ/literature_repository/papers/Calibration%203D_Reconstruction/2011%20Calibration%20of%20housing%20parameters%20for%20underwater%20stereo-camera%20rigs.pdf">
