<node TEXT="We found this method to compute absolute pose more robustly than the methods described by Nist&#x2032;er and Stew&#x2032;enius in [22] or Sturm et al. in [26], whose solutions work on a minimum number of 3 required 2D-3D correspondences. The reason is that underwater images suffer&#xd;&#xa;from degraded contrast. Consequently, the correspondences&#xd;&#xa;have a certain amount of noise, and hence a method that is more robust against noise but may require more than the minimal number of 3 correspondences can outperform [22] and [26] within a RANSAC framework.&#xd;&#xa;2D-3D correspondences&#x6307;&#x7684;&#x5230;&#x5e95;&#x662f;&#x4ec0;&#x4e48;&#xff1f;&#x4ece;&#x4e0b;&#x6587;&#x770b;&#xff0c;&#x4e0d;&#x662f;&#x6821;&#x6b63;&#x677f;&#x4e0a;&#x7684;&#x70b9;&#xff0c;&#x662f;&#x4e09;&#x7ef4;&#x7ed3;&#x6784;&#x4e2d;&#x7684;&#x5df2;&#x77e5;&#x70b9;&#x5417;&#xff1f;&#x662f;&#x600e;&#x4e48;&#x83b7;&#x53d6;&#x7684;&#xff1f;" ID="ID_1871250108" CREATED="1501313514760" MODIFIED="1501313514760" LINK="project://15D6452E29D9SKCYL8S32EEF1MB7Z0BV75KJ/literature_repository/papers/Calibration%203D_Reconstruction/2013%20Refractive%20structure-from-motion%20on%20Underwater%20Images.pdf">
